WE send you herewith the body of James Sybbold, Doctor in Divinity, being a Scot, and remaining in England without license, contrary to an Act of Parliament, August 2. Anno 1651 by wh
                              •
                           ch Act the said offence is made Treason; you shall therefore detern him in your safe Custody, untill by due course of Law he shall be delivered. And this shall be your Warrant;
